<section id="katas">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto">
        <h1 class="mt-5">Katayuno</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Katayuno (Katas + Desayuno) is a weekly open event where to pair code katas to learn TDD while enjoying a freshly baked breakfast.

          <p>If youâ€™d like to know more about Katayuno, check out <a href="https://medium.com/@FlywireEng/katayuno-c2c19c65e66a", target="_blank">this</a> article.</p>
        </p>
        <h2>The kata</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          A code kata is a small exercise in programming that is meant to help us programmers sharpen our skills through practice.
        </p>
        <h2>The TDD</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          TDD is a software development process that uses tests to make the design emerge by following the red/green/refactor cycle.
        </p>
        <h2>The pairing</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Pair programming is an agile software development technique in which two programmers work together at one workstation.
        </p>
        <h2>The Language</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          You can make katas in every languages, the important point is to learn tdd, good practices and pairing.
        </p>
        <h2>The meetup</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          The <a href="https://www.meetup.com/es-ES/Aprende-a-programar-en-Valencia/events/242889981/", target="_blank">meetup</a> is hosted by <a href="https://www.flywire.com/", target="_blank">Flywire</a> and organized by <a href="http://www.devscola.org", target="_blank">Devscola</a>.
        </p>
